<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="42" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No.3382/19.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St. Josse Ten
                                        Noode</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-20"><hi rend="italic">December 20,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Wilson reports that the title of the new King of Belgium will be
                            Albert I, and that the ceremony of enthronement will take place on the
                            23d instant. He adds that the diplomatists will be received on the
                            24th.</p>
                    </div>
